title: Investments by National Banks, Other Than Central for United States
notes:
Monthly Coverage Varies Form Year To Year. Except For 1882, Which Only Has Data For October And December, All Years 1883-1913 Have Scattered Five Month Coverage. Six Months Are Presented For 1914. Investments Called "Other Stocks And Bonds", "Other Bonds, Securities, Etc.", Etc. In Source. Other Reserve Cities Exclude Chicago And St. Louis. Source: Computed By NBER From Figures In Annual Reports Of The Comptroller Of The Currency.

This NBER data series m14039 appears on the NBER website in Chapter 14 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter14.html.
